    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MBSFN Subframe Configuration in rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB13\n\n### Summary\nThe function `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB13` was missing MBSFN subframe configuration for SIB2, causing resource allocation conflicts. This fix adds the missing SIB2 MBSFN configuration handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_M2AP.c`: Added SIB2 MBSFN subframe configuration handling in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB13`\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_M2AP.c`: Updated variable declarations and mac configuration call\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen configuring MBSFN with eMBMS enabled, UEs experience resource allocation conflicts because SIB2 was not properly configured with MBSFN subframe allocation information. This leads to:\n- Incorrect resource block allocation\n- Scheduling conflicts between normal data and MBSFN transmissions\n- Potential data loss or transmission failures\n\nThe issue can be observed when running eMBMS scenarios where UEs fail to properly decode MBSFN transmissions due to missing subframe allocation information.\n\n"
}